FBIS3-30962 "dreeu030aa_94014" FBIS-EEU-94-030 Document Type:Daily Report 14 February 1994 INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Talks on Bosnia Peace Continue in Geneva Karadzic Threatens To Secede LD1302094794 Bern Swiss Radio International in English 0900 GMT 13 Feb 94 LD1302094794 Bern Swiss Radio International Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] The ethnic Serbian leader says ethnic Serbians will unilaterally secede with territory they hold if the Muslims continue to reject the latest map dividing Bosnia into three states. Radovan Karadzic made the statement after peace talks in Geneva ended in deadlock on Saturday.
